      "symbol": "host"
    }
  ],
  "text": "The deprecated `req.host` property is referenced in three source files within the sg-evals/expressjs-express repository:\n\n1. **lib/request.js** (lines 454-456): This file contains the definition of the deprecated `req.host` property. It is defined as a deprecated getter function using `deprecate.function()` that returns `this.hostname` and emits the deprecation warning 'req.host: Use req.hostname instead'. A TODO comment at line 452 indicates the intent to change this behavior in the next major version.\n\n2. **test/req.host.js**: This test file contains comprehensive test cases for the `req.host` property, with multiple test cases at lines 12, 25, 39, 51, 64, 80, 96, 112, and 128. The tests verify various behaviors including: returning the Host header when present, stripping port numbers, handling IPv6 addresses with and without ports, respecting X-Forwarded-Host when trust proxy is enabled, and handling cases where no Host header is present.\n\n3. **History.md** (changelog): The changelog contains 9 references to `req.host` across different versions:\n   - Line 2726: Initial addition of req.host feature\n   - Line 2552: Added X-Forwarded-Host support\n   - Line 2514: Fix for missing Host header\n   - Line 2368: Fix for IPv6 literals\n   - Line 1653: Fix for trust proxy hops count\n   - Line 1436: Fix for IPv6 literals\n   - Line 1286: Deprecation notice for req.host\n   - Line 1284: Introduction of req.hostname as the correct property name\n   - Line 799: Fix for trust proxy hops count\n\nAll references have been verified to be for the standalone deprecated `req.host` property and not part of the non-deprecated `req.hostname` property."
}

